-- out.txt --
Scanned 1 Go file and 0 Buf templates. The generated Connect code still
targets v1, so no Go source changes are proposed yet.

Generated v1 Connect SDKs (the go get @v2 below updates these):
  buf.build/gen/go/example/test/connectrpc/go

First, move the dependencies and generated code to v2:

  1. go get -u \
       connectrpc.com/connect/v2 \
       buf.build/gen/go/example/test/connectrpc/go@v2 \
       connectrpc.com/otelconnect/v2
     (pulls the v2 core, generated SDKs, and ecosystem modules into go.mod)

Then re-run connect-go-v2-migrate to work through the Go source changes: it
rewrites the call sites against the v2 stubs and reports anything that needs
a manual update.

Full migration guide: https://github.com/connectrpc/connect-go/blob/main/docs/v2-migration.md
